The paper deals with motion planning of a multi-agent system, which is a typical topic in the field of multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The paper also involves the transportation of objects by the agents, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of temporal logic formulas to specify the agents' and objects' specifications suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The design of control protocols for the agents and objects implies the use of control theory (cs.SY). Finally, the simulation results verify the proposed framework, which suggests the involvement of machine learning (cs.LG) in the implementation of the framework.
